<figureCitation box="[817,890,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1597,1621]" captionTargetBox="[266,1316,901,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[258,1329,890,1575]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A, Pedionis (Pedionis) yunnana sp. nov., male; B &amp; C, Pedionis (Pedionis) yunnana, sp. nov. female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195497/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[875,890,896,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C) strongly convex on anterior margin. 
<collectingCountry box="[1376,1436,896,922]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial spinulation R 
<number box="[375,383,949,963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[391,421,933,959]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="11.0">11</number>
, R 
<number box="[453,461,949,963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[468,485,933,959]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="9.0">9</number>
, R 
<number box="[517,525,949,963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[533,550,933,959]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
